This paper involves the use of classification algorithms to identify hazardousness of sewer pipeline gas mixture. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). As the paper deals with the detection of toxic gases, it may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of dataset and experiments, which may make it relevant to the sub-categories of Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
